# Makefile All-Extras for Local Development

**Session**: Changed `shared/python.mk` to use `uv sync --all-extras` instead of selective `--extra dev` (with conditional `--extra gpu`), so local development always gets every optional dependency — including `[finetune]` (HuggingFace Hub, transformers, etc.), `[compute]` (Modal), `[vault-health]` (networkx), and `[gpu]` (torch).

## What changed

- `shared/python.mk` — `$(VENV_DIR)/activate` and `install` targets switched from `uv sync --extra dev $(GPU_EXTRA_UV)` to `uv sync --all-extras`
- `shared/python.mk` — `install-gpu` target similarly switched to `--all-extras` (was `--extra dev --extra gpu`)
- `shared/python.mk` — removed unused `GPU_EXTRA` and `GPU_EXTRA_UV` variables (no longer needed since `--all-extras` covers GPU unconditionally)

## Rationale

The `[finetune]` extra (huggingface_hub, tokenizers, transformers, etc.) was not included in the default dev setup. Importing models from HuggingFace Hub through the web UI failed with `missing_extra: Install anvil[finetune] to import from HuggingFace Hub`. Rather than add yet another selective `--extra finetune` flag, we switched to `--all-extras` — this is a local dev workflow where installing all optional deps is the right default.

